description:
The purpose of   scriptural review is to develop biblical insights, principles, theories, and concepts to inform decision-making, problem-solving, identification of  Theowordiness  gaps or word gaps in existing research, develop research questions, and inform research design from a biblical frame of reference. Scriptural review brings a deeper understanding and correct interpretation of God&rsquo;s word. This ground-breaking paper proposes and   explores the necessity of a paradigm shift from traditional literature reviews to scriptural reviews in biblical research studies. The paper argues that a scriptural review is essential for accurate biblical interpretation, theological understanding, and effective scholarly writing in biblical research studies. However, the author asserts that tripartite or triangulation reviews can be conducted for a comprehensive and nuanced understanding, but scriptural review takes precedence over other types of reviews because the Bible is the fulcrum on which biblical research or theological studies is based.   The paper also intends to demonstrate the degree of scriptural citations in some seemingly biblical Christian academic works to determine their  Theowordiness.  The review of relevant scriptural texts in biblical research is to ensure the accuracy, depth, and relevance of biblical scholarly findings.  The author adopts a sola scriptura research methodology, expository paradigm, and a theoretical triangulation within the biblical theological paradigm to establish the imperative of scriptural review in biblical research or theological studies.   
   &nbsp;   
   Keywords:     scriptural review, sola scriptura research methodology, theowordiness, biblical research studie, paradigm shift from literature review

